OL,3,CMan jailed for murdering lodger and
OL,4,Cscattering body parts
OL,6,FA man who murdered his lodger in a
OL,7,F"ferocious attack" before scattering
OL,8,Fhis body parts along Bournemouth
OL,9,Fseafront has been jailed for a minimum
OL,10,Fof 19 years.
OL,12,F49-year old Benjamin Lee Atkins
OL,13,Fattacked Simon Shotton, also 49, with
OL,14,Fa knife at his home in Aylesbury Road,
OL,15,FBoscombe, following a disagreement
OL,16,Fover money in August 2023.
OL,18,FA police investigation was launched
OL,19,Fafter Mr Shotton's legs were found in
OL,20,Fpackages by a member of the public on
OL,21,Fthe Manor Steps Zig Zag footpath.
