OL,3,CMan jailed for murdering lodger and
OL,4,Cscattering body parts
OL,6,FAtkins admitted in court to killing Mr
OL,7,FShotton at the couple's home and
OL,8,Fdismembering his body, but claimed he
OL,9,Fhad acted out of self-defence.
OL,11,FMr Shotton's son, Wesley, branded his
OL,12,Ffather's killer "evil" as he said:
OL,13,F"Your children should be ashamed of
OL,14,Fwhat you have done. You wrecked so
OL,15,Fmany more lives than just my
OL,17,Fdad's. No sentence will ever be enough
OL,18,Ffor what you have done."
