OL,4,Cscattering body parts
OL,6,FAddressing Atkins, Mrs Justice Stacey
OL,7,Fsaid: "Your dismemberment, disposal
OL,8,Fand concealment of Mr Shotton's body
OL,9,Fwas particularly gruesome. Your
OL,10,Fcallousness was shocking.
OL,12,F"You may have initially acted to some
OL,13,Fextent in self-defence, but with the
OL,14,Fferocity of your attack, you intended
OL,15,Fto kill Simon."
OL,17,FSentencing Pereira, the judge said:
OL,18,F"As a consequence of the help you gave
OL,19,FAtkins, parts of Simon have never been
OL,20,Ffound. You were in it together, before
OL,21,Fand after Atkins killed Simon.
